ttisgarh's%20Tulsi%20village%20got%20its%20own%20'Hummer%20Studios'%20soon%20after%20several%20YouTube%20channels%20like%20Being%20Chhattisgarhiya%2C%2036%20Garhiya%2C%20Alwa%20Jalwa%2C%20Fun%20Tapri%20and%20Gold%20CG04%20took%20off.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Guest%20Contributor%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F337583%2Ftulsi-village-chhattisgarh-youtube-village-hummer-studios-being-chhattisgarhiya-alwa-jalwa-gold-cg04%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reasons%20For%20CERT-IN's%20Exemption%20From%20RTI%20Provisions%20Are%20%E2%80%98Secret%E2%80%99%2C%20DoPT%20Says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F12193303%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-12-at-7.32.14-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20and%20Training%20(DoPT)%20has%20refused%20to%20disclose%20documentary%20records%20that%20exempt%20the%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20(CERT-IN)%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CERT%20is%20the%20national%20nodal%20agency%20for%20responding%20to%20computer%20security%20incidents%20as%20and%20when%20they%20occur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20was%20sought%20by%20RTI%20activist%20Venkatesh%20Nayak%20following%20a%20gazette%20notification%20on%20November%2023%2C%20which%20stated%20that%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20was%20amended%20to%20include%20the%20CERT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20implies%20that%20the%20CERT%20will%20be%20exempt%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20except%20in%20cases%20where%20the%20information%20is%20sought%20in%20cases%20of%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20or%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20RTI%20request%2C%20Nayak%20sought%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20cabinet%20note%20relating%20to%20the%20amendment%20of%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%20the%20note%20put%20up%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20committee%20of%20secretaries%20containing%20the%20proposal%20relating%20to%20the%20said%20amendment%2C%20a%20copy%20of%20all%20documents%20relating%20to%20the%20inter-ministerial%20consultations%20held%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20said%20amendment%20proposal%20till%20date%2C%20along%20with%20all%20file%20notings%20and%20correspondence%20held%20in%20paper%20and%20electronic%20form%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20said%20amendment%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20sought%20a%20copy%20of%20all%20official%20records%20demonstrating%20compliance%20with%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20DoPT%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20then-joint%20secretary%2C%20Devesh%20Chaturvedi%2C%20in%202015%20regarding%20the%20procedure%20for%20notifying%20new%20organisations%20under%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20aforementioned%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENayak%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20request%20referred%20to%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20in%202015%20that%20proper%20guidelines%20be%20adopted%20to%20ensure%20wide%20public%20consultation%20prior%20to%20any%20body%20being%20exempted%20from%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20recommended%20that%20prior%20to%20the%20government%20issuing%20a%20notification%20under%20Section%2024(2)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20empowers%20it%20to%20amend%20the%20second%20schedule%20%E2%80%93%20the%20name%20of%20the%20proposed%20body%2C%20the%20details%20of%20its%20functioning%20and%20an%20explanation%20on%20how%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20responds%20to%20grounds%20set%20out%20under%20Section%2024%20should%20be%20publicly%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20specified%20time-frame%20should%20be%20allowed%20for%20members%20of%20the%20public%20to%20raise%20objections%20to%20the%20proposal%2C%20the%20committee%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20also%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20proactive%20disclosures%20required%20under%20Sections%204(c)%20and%20(d)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20the%20Pre-Legislative%20Consultation%20Policy%20(PCLP)%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20notifications%20under%20Section%2024%20by%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20must%20comprehensively%20and%20explicitly%20specify%20how%20the%20organisation%20that%20is%20being%20exempted%20fits%20into%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintelligence%20and%20security%20organisations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20reply%20on%20December%2028%2C%202023%2C%20the%20DoPT%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CSection%2024%20of%20the%20RTI%20act%20provides%20that%20nothing%20contained%20in%20this%20Act%20shall%20apply%20to%20the%20intelligence%20and%20security%20organisations%20specified%20in%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20proposal%20of%20exemption%20of%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20RTI%20Act%20has%20been%20dealt%20in%20File%20No.%201%2F3%2F2021-IR%20II%20which%20relates%20to%20amendment%20in%20second%20schedule%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20the%20information%20regarding%20CERT%E2%80%99s%20inclusion%20in%20the%20second%20schedule%20was%20of%20%E2%80%9Csecret%20nature.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20information%20provided%20by%20the%20organisations%20concerned%20including%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20for%20their%20inclusion%20in%20the%20second%20schedule%20is%20of%20secret%20nature%20and%20exempted%20under%20Section%208(1)(a)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20i.e.%20information%2C%20disclosure%20of%20which%20would%20prejudicially%20affect%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20the%20security%2C%20strategic%2C%20scientific%20or%20economic%20interests%20of%20the%20state%2C%20relation%20with%20foreign%20state%20or%20lead%20to%20incitement%20of%20an%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20information%20is%20also%20exempted%20under%20Section%208(1)(i)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20being%20record%20of%20deliberations%20of%20Secretaries%20and%20other%20officers%20and%20part%20of%20the%20Note%20for%20Committee%20of%20Secretaries%20which%20itself%20is%20Secret%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%202015%20committee%20recommendations%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20accepted%20by%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHence%2C%20compliance%20with%20the%20said%20recommendations%20does%20not%20arise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Nayak%20said%20that%20the%20refusal%20to%20provide%20the%20documents%20is%20%E2%80%9Cintriguing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20refusal%20is%20simply%20intriguing%20because%20when%20the%20NDA%20government%20decided%20to%20include%20the%20Strategic%20Forces%20Command%20(SFC)%20under%20the%20excluded%20list%2C%20the%20CPIO%20gave%20me%20all%20the%20information%20including%20file%20noting%20and%20correspondence%20and%20the%20note%20put%20up%20to%20the%20committee%20of%20secretaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20looks%20like%20the%20Government%20is%20treating%20CERT-IN%20as%20more%20strategic%20to%20our%20security%20interests%20than%20the%20SFC%2C%20which%20looks%20after%20our%20strategic%20and%20defence%20assets%20including%20nuclear%20weapons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704463203000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F12193303%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-12-at-7.32.14-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Finfo-on-cert-in-inclusion-rti-exempt-orgs-is-secret%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Activist%20Venkatesh%20Nayak%20had%20sought%20to%20know%20through%20an%20RTI%20filed%20in%20November%20about%20the%20deliberations%20behind%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20CERT-IN%20in%20the%20list%20of%20organisations%20that%20are%20exempt%20from%20the%20RTI%20Act's%20ambit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Finfo-on-cert-in-inclusion-rti-exempt-orgs-is-secret%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20Rs%20259%20Crore%2C%20BJP%20Received%2070%25%20of%20Donations%20by%20Electoral%20Trusts%20in%202022-23%3A%20ECI%20Data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01145249%2F406110211_773446158163006_4756603232278021214_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20received%20over%2070%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations%20by%20electoral%20trusts%20in%202022-23%2C%20according%20to%20data%20shared%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20saffron%20party%20received%20Rs%20259.08%20crore%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%20366%20crore%20collected%20by%20five%20electoral%20trusts%20that%20submitted%20their%20annual%20reports%20to%20the%20ECI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20corporate%20donation%20of%20Rs%2087%20crore%20came%20from%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructures.%20Serum%20Institute%20of%20India%20and%20ArcelorMittal%20Nippon%20Steel%20gave%20Rs%2050.25%20crore%20and%20Rs%2050%20crore%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20political%20funding%20through%20these%20trusts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20trusts%20were%20introduced%20by%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance-II%20regime%20in%202013%20to%20facilitate%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20by%20corporations%20and%20individuals.%20However%2C%20unlike%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20trusts%20are%20supposed%20to%20declare%20their%20donation%20reports%20to%20the%20ECI%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20trusts%20are%20required%20by%20rules%20to%20distribute%20at%20least%2095%25%20of%20their%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%20In%202022-23%2C%20however%2C%20these%20trusts%20distributed%2099.99%25%20of%20their%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022-23%2C%2013%20out%20of%20the%2018%20electoral%20trusts%2C%20registered%20with%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%2C%20submitted%20their%20reports%20to%20the%20ECI.%20The%20reports%20show%20that%20only%20five%20trusts%20received%20donations%20from%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%20366%20crore%20received%20by%20the%20five%20trusts%20from%2039%20corporates%2C%20over%2090%25%20contributions%20came%20from%2010%20business%20houses%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20shows.%20Out%20of%20the%20total%20donations%2C%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%20alone%20received%20Rs%20360.46%20crore%2C%20with%20Rs%20332.26%20crore%20coming%20from%20the%20top%2010%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221173%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688.png%201173w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688-300x141.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688-1024x483.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691774%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22553%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20ADR%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20only%20one%20company%20contributed%20Rs%202%20crore%20to%20Samaj%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20two%20companies%20contributed%20Rs%2075.50%20lakh%20to%20Paribartan%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20and%20two%20companies%20contributed%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20to%20Triumph%20Electoral%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2011%20individuals%20contributed%20to%20electoral%20trusts%20in%202022-23.%20%E2%80%9CEight%20individuals%20contributed%20Rs%202.70%20crore%20to%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20three%20individuals%20contributed%20Rs%208%20lakh%20to%20Einzigartig%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ADR%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrudent%20Electoral%20Trust%20donated%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20its%20contributions%20to%20the%20BJP%20(Rs%20256.25%20crore).%20It%20donated%20the%20rest%20of%20its%20donations%20to%20other%20political%20parties%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(Rs%2090%20crore)%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%20Rs%2017%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20YSR%20Congress%2C%20and%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamaj%20donated%20Rs%201.50%20crore%20to%20the%20saffron%20party.%20The%20Congress%20received%20only%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20from%20Samaj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190037%2Fimage-1689.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22863%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190037%2Fimage-1689.png%20863w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190037%2Fimage-1689-300x153.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691770%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22441%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20ADR%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrudent%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20earlier%20known%20as%20Satya%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20has%20consistently%20received%20the%20maximum%20share%20of%20contributions%20among%20all%20the%20other%20registered%20electoral%20trusts.%20Among%20its%20donors%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Fcorporate%2Fstory%2Fprudent-electoral-trust-richest-trust-gives-rs-144-cr-of-rs-169-cr-funds-bjp-fy18-154942-2018-11-05%5C%22%3E%20are%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20business%20conglomerates%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20the%20DLF%20group%2C%20Bharti%20group%2C%20UPL%2C%20Torrent%20Power%2C%20DCM%20Shriram%2C%20Cadia%20Group%2C%20Haldia%20Energy%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20It%20was%20set%20up%20before%20the%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20and%20operated%20out%20of%20Bharti%20group%E2%80%99s%20premises%20in%20Vasant%20Kunj%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20with%20the%20support%20of%20around%2033%20companies%20associated%20with%20the%20Sunil%20Mittal-led%20corporation.%20Later%2C%20its%20office%20was%20shifted%20to%20Hans%20Bhawan%20on%20Bahadur%20Shah%20Zafar%20Marg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Bharti%20group%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20Prudent%20is%20not%20only%20backed%20by%20the%20company%20but%20also%20by%20other%20corporates%2C%20such%20as%20Hero%20MotoCorp%2C%20National%20Engineering%20Industries%2C%20Gmmco%2C%20Jubilant%20FoodWorks%2C%20Orient%20Cement%2C%20DLF%2C%20JK%20Tyre%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EPrint%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Freport%2Findias-biggest-political-funding-trust-backed-bharti-enterprises%2F35370%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20most%20of%20Bharti%20Airtel%20executives%20hold%20directorial%20positions%20at%20the%20trust%2C%20with%20promoter%20companies%20like%20%E2%80%9CDM%20Buildwell%2C%20which%20is%20headed%20by%20Bharti%20vice-chairman%20Rakesh%20Bharti%20Mittal%2C%20Bharti%20Realty%2C%20Bharti%20Realty%20Holdings%2C%20Bharti%20(SBM)%20Holdings%2C%20and%20Meh